tats/com.typesafe.play/play-configuration_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:312:| `com.typesafe.play:play-exceptions` | [2.9.7<br>- 2.9.11](metadata/com.typesafe.play/play-exceptions/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Play Exceptions provides the core Play Framework exception types used to carry structured error details such as titles, descriptions, source locations, attachments, and rich HTML descriptions. It supports Play's developer error reporting by exposing reusable exception classes that can identify relevant source lines and attach additional diagnostic content.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/com.typesafe.play/play-exceptions/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:313:| `com.typesafe.play:play-functional_2.13` | [2.10.8](metadata/com.typesafe.play/play-functional_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Play Functional provides the Scala functional-programming building blocks used by Play JSON, including functors, applicatives, monoids, reducers, and product builders. It lets Scala applications compose validation, reading, and writing logic through Play's play.api.libs.functional APIs.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/com.typesafe.play/play-functional_2.13/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:314:| `com.typesafe.play:play-functional_3` | [2.10.6<br>- 2.10.8](metadata/com.typesafe.play/play-functional_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Play Functional provides the functional combinator abstractions and syntax used by Play JSON, including functors, applicatives, monoids, and product builders. It supplies reusable Scala APIs for composing validation, reading, and writing logic in Play-based data transformations.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/com.typesafe.play/play-functional_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:315:| `com.typesafe.play:play-json_3` | [2.10.6<br>- 2.10.8](metadata/com.typesafe.play/play-json_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Play JSON provides Scala APIs for parsing, generating, validating, transforming, and serializing JSON through JsValue, Reads, Writes, and Format abstractions. The play-json_3 artifact is the Scala 3 JVM build and can be used both inside Play Framework applications and as a standalone JSON library.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/com.typesafe.play/play-json_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:316:| `com.typesafe.play:play-ws_2.13` | [2.9.10<br>- 2.9.11](metadata/com.typesafe.play/play-ws_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Play WS provides Play Framework's HTTP web service client APIs for Scala and Java, including request, response, body reader, and body writer abstractions. It adapts Play-specific request and response types to the standalone WS client implementation used for asynchronous HTTP calls.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/com.typesafe.play/play-ws_2.13/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:317:| `com.typesafe.play:play_2.13` | [2.9.10<br>- 2.9.11](metadata/com.typesafe.play/play_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Play Framework is a JVM web framework for building scalable, stateless applications in Java and Scala with asynchronous request handling, routing, controllers, templating, JSON, WebSocket, and asset support. This play_2.13 artifact provides the Scala 2.13 core Play APIs and runtime pieces used by Play applications and related Play modules.</details> | [100.0% (41/41 calls)](stats/com.typesafe.play/play_2.13/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:318:| `com.typesafe.play:twirl-api_2.13` | [1.6.10](metadata/com.typesafe.play/twirl-api_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Twirl API provides the runtime API for Play Framework's Twirl template engine, including content types, formats, escaping utilities, and template interfaces used by generated templates. It lets Scala and Java applications render HTML, XML, JavaScript, and text templates either inside Play projects or as a standalone templating layer.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/com.typesafe.play/twirl-api_2.13/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:319:| `com.typesafe.play:twirl-api_3` | [1.6.9<br>- 1.6.10](metad